    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>April 12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1858</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Your esteemed favor of <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>
                ultimo<lb/> duly came to hand; as did also the Package of Booksâ€”<lb/> the contents
                of which were distributed strictly in accordance<lb/> with your instructions.
                    <persName>M. S. Friend</persName> declined taking the<lb/> Occident to his
                address, saying he was not a subscriber, and<lb/> I regret to say,
                    <persName>Boyds</persName> carrier returned one Number from which<lb/> he had
                lost the direction and it is impossible for me to tell<lb/> to whom it belongs,
                although I will endeavor to find out<lb/>
                <persName>Mr B. Cohen</persName> has paid his bill of $6. as has also a Bijin<lb/>
                paid his of $2.50.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I send by <persName>Adams &amp; Co.</persName> the package received
                last month<lb/> from <persName>J. Hart Senr</persName> of
                    <placeName>Charleston</placeName>, having found no private<lb/> opportunity to
                which I could send it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have read the last number of the Occident with unusual<lb/>
                interest, more particularly the portions relating to your good self<lb/> personally.
                I had not previously any just conception of the<lb/> extent of your persecutions by
                Secret for who seem to have had<lb/> no scruples as to the means used to inflict
                injury &amp; <hi rend="underline">insult</hi>.<lb/> I hope however you will soon
                triumph over them all and<lb/> make them bite the dust.</p>
            <p>With kindest regards to <persName>Mrs Cozens</persName> &amp; the young ladies.</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">I remain Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Hanford</persName>
            </p>
